    "Model trainingThree models namely Normal Forecaster, Extreme Forecaster, and extreme value classifier are trained as below.",
    "Normal Forecaster: It is an LSTM-based model for forecasting normal values in time series that involves several key components to effectively capture temporal dependencies and produce accurate predictions.",
    "It begins with an input layer that is of 100 units of LSTM Cells followed by a batch normalization layer.",
    "The LSTM model contains a total 4 layers each of 100 cells of LSTM units and followed by batch normalization layers.",
    "The output from the LSTM layers is fed into a dense (fully connected) layer, which maps the learned features to the final output."
